cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper presents a method that combines a variational autoencoder (VAE) with a generative adversarial network (GAN) to improve similarity measures in data space. This involves learning feature representations in the GAN discriminator that are used as the basis for the VAE reconstruction objective. The method is applied to images of faces and shows improved visual fidelity and the ability to modify high-level abstract visual features. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also possible sub-categories given the use of neural networks and image data.
